The following instructions describe the steps to compile the mudlet source for Ubuntu.

1. First you need to installed the required dependencies:

a) sudo apt-get install build-essential qt4-dev-tools libqt4-opengl-dev lua5.1 liblua5.1-0-dev liblua5.1-rex-pcre-dev liblua5.1-sql-sqlite3-dev libpcre3-dev libboost1.40-dev zlib1g-dev libyajl-dev libzzip-dev liblua5.1-filesystem* liblua5.1-zip*

2. Download and install QtSDK

a) download the SDK from http://qt.nokia.com/downloads

b) chmod u+x the file to make it executable and then run to install.

3. install pythonqt

a) set your python version:
cd /path to git clone/mudlet/src/pythonqt/build
gedit python.prf
Change the version number in this line: PYTHON_VERSION=2.6 if you are using a newer or older version of python (ie 2.5 or 2.7).

b) go to the pythonqt source dirctory:
cd /path to git clone/mudlet/src/pythonqt/src

c) qmake

d) make

e) Create pythonqt folder in /usr/lib:
cd /usr/lib
sudo mkdir pythonqt

f) move the library across:
cp /path to git clone/mudlet/src/pythonqt/lib/* /usr/lib/pythonqt/

g) create new ld configuration file:
sudo gedit /etc/ld.so.conf.d/PythonQt.conf

h) add the below line and save:
/usr/lib/pythonqt

i) run ldconfig:
sudo ldconfig

4. compile mudlet

a) go to the mudlet src directory:
cd /path to git clone/mudlet/src/

b) qmake

c) make

5. Run mudlet:
./mudlet
